@olegmoz it seems to me that using separate interfaces Counter and Gauge will lower cohesion because those two interfaces will operate on the same set of encapsulated data. I propose two alternatives:
Only one interface:
interface Metrics {
     void inc();
     void add(int num);
     void set(long val);
     long value(); 
}
or split metrics to two different interfaces CounterMetrics GaugeMetrics. wdyt?
